Crono (Version 1.3.6) - Tue Jun 29 16:51:16 BRT 2004

* cralloc: Now it is not necessary to specify a file to perform qualitative
           allocation. But it is still possible to use it.
           Examples:
                 cralloc -n p3-550:8
                      or
                 cralloc -n "p3-550:8 p4-2g:4" (double commas are needed when
                                                more than one node type is
                                                defined)

* Documentation: Updated

