Crono (Version 1.3.3) - Tue May 11 15:59:49 BRT 2004

* crrmd: The "#! interpreter [arg]" and the execution permission of
        the Master and User Pre and Post Processing Scripts as well as
        batch job script are not needed anymore.
        The mpreps.sh, mpostps.sh, <cluster>.upreps.sh and <cluster>.upostps.sh
        were replaced by mpreps, mpostps, <cluster>.upreps
        and <cluster>.upostps.

* bug fixed: In some cases, users making quantitative allocations receive more
             nodes of some types than they should receive. For this reason,
             when a quantitative allocation is done, the Access Manager sends
             the user access rights to the Request Manager.

* Documentation: Updated (thanks Matheus Rodrigues for the suggestions)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
